{
  "upload_type": "software",
  "title": "Formogenhetsanalys: graph-aware estimation of wealth concentration in Sweden",
  "description": "<p>Formogenhetsanalys is a Python research-software package for network-aware estimation and decomposition of wealth concentration in Sweden. It represents households, closely held firms (famansforetag), foundations, and ownership chains as a typed heterogeneous graph and deploys edge-typed message-passing graph neural networks with Bayesian shrinkage priors and variational inference over latent beneficial-ownership shares. Valuation harmonisation modules reconcile listed equity, residential real estate, and unlisted equity valuations. Distributional National Accounts adjustments align top-share estimates with World Inequality Lab methodology.</p>",
  "creators": [
    {
      "name": "Laitinen-Fredriksson Lundstrom Imanov, Gustav Olaf Yunus",
      "affiliation": "Department of Economics, Stockholm University",
